Sentencas: Preparation and performance of bimetallic Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ anodes were tested to overcome common deficiencies of carbon and Sulfur poisoning in SOFCs.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: Ni1-xCoxO-YSZ and Ni(1-x)CuxO-YSZ precursors were synthesized via co-precipitation of their respective chlorides.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: Single cell solid oxide fuel cells of these bimetallic anodes were tested ill H-2, CH4, and H2S/CH4 fuel mixtures.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: Addition Of Cu2+ into the NiO lattice resulted in large metal particle sizes and decreased SOFC performance.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: Addition of Co2+ into the NiO lattice to form Ni0.92Co0.08O-YSZ anode precursor produced a cermet with a large BET Surface area and active metal Surface area, thus increasing the rate of hydrogen oxidation for this sample.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: The performance of both bimetallics was found to quickly degrade in dry CH4 Clue to carbon deposition and lifting of the anode from the electrolyte.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: However, Ni0.69Co0.31-YSZ showed superior activity in a 10% (v/v) H2S/CH4 fuel mixture, Surpassing performance with H-2 fuel, thereby demonstrating the exciting prospect of using sulfidated Ni(1-x)Cox-YSZ as SOFC anodes in sulfur containing methane streams.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: The active anode becomes a sulfidated alloy (Ni-Co-S) under operating conditions.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S

Sentencas: This anode showed enhanced performance, which surpassed those of sulfidated Ni and Co anodes, thereby Suggesting a synergistic behaviour in the Ni-Co-S anode.
Titulo: Synergistic effects of Ni1-xCox-YSZ and Ni1-xCux-YSZ alloyed cermet SOFC anodes for oxidation of hydrogen and methane fuels containing H2S
